# ==============================================
# ARC PAY - TOKEN EXCHANGE (SWAP) SETUP
# This is the ONLY file you need to make the swap work.
# Follow the steps in order. No confusion.
# ==============================================
#
# WHAT THIS DOES:
# The swap (USDC <-> EURC on Arc Testnet) uses Circle App Kit.
# It requires the key to be present at BUILD TIME as NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY.
# This matches exactly how the working demo at https://elementswap-eta.vercel.app/ is set up.
#
# STEP-BY-STEP (DO EXACTLY IN THIS ORDER):
#
# 1. Copy this entire file.
#
# 2. Replace ONLY the line below with your real key.
#    The value must start with "KIT_KEY:" (copy the full thing you received from Circle).
#
# 3. Save the file as "vercel.env" (or any name).
#
# 4. Go to Vercel:
#    https://vercel.com/siribraheems-projects/arcpay-web-app
#
# 5. Project Settings → Environment Variables
#
# 6. Click the big "Import" button.
#    - Select the file you just saved.
#    - IMPORTANT: Make sure "Production", "Preview", and "Development" are all checked.
#
# 7. Click Import.
#
# 8. Go to the "Deployments" tab.
#
# 9. Find the most recent "Production" deployment.
#    Click the three dots (...) → "Redeploy".
#
# 10. Wait for it to say READY (green).
#
# 11. Hard refresh your site (Ctrl/Cmd + Shift + R).
#     Go to Dashboard → Token Exchange panel.
#
# The yellow banner will disappear and the swap will work (same as the demo).
#
# TROUBLESHOOTING (if still shows key error):
# - Double-check you used the name NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY (not KIT_KEY).
# - You MUST click Redeploy after importing the variables.
# - The key value must be the FULL string starting with KIT_KEY:...
#
# NEVER commit a file containing your real key to GitHub.

NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_FULL_KEY_HERE_STARTING_WITH_KIT_KEY_COLON

# (Optional) Privy login
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PRIVY_APP_ID=your-privy-app-id-here
